{
  "texts": [
    "• Structure (i.e.",
    "conceptual schema): This refers to how different variables relate to each other within a dataset; these can vary widely across datasets.",
    "On one end of the spectrum is structured data, which are highly organized and formatted (e.g.",
    "data tables), to unstructured data with little or no fixed format (e.g. raw text, images).",
    "Different datasets can have large sources of variation not only across types of data structures but within them."
  ]
}